description: The finest in Japanese cuisine since 1985, Tokyo is the first Japanese restaurant in the kingdom of Saudi Arabia, serving modern fusion Japanese menu in a stylish environment with an up-scale sushi bar, Tea bar, Private room, and Teppanyaki rooms with live cooking where you have your private Chef and Butler. Known for having the best sushi rolls in town and the menu is diversified with all popular mouth-watering Japanese items from Sushi to Maki, Sashimi, Ramen, Noodles, Salads, Beef steak, chicken katsu, Udon, Black cod, and much more. Recognized by many F&B experts and got nominated and shortlisted on international awards lists. You can find us on our flagship branch AlUrubah Rd or Veranda F&B complex north ring road to enjoy the terrace.

name: لوسين
description: Lusin Restaurant is a unique dining experience that transports you to the vibrant culture of Armenia. Our menu features a wide range of traditional Armenian dishes, each expertly crafted to showcase the unique flavors and aromas of this rich and vibrant culture. From savory kebabs and stuffed grape leaves, to sweet pastries and aromatic coffee, there is something for everyone at Lusin. As you dine, enjoy the lively Armenian music and take in the cultural atmosphere of the restaurant, which is adorned with colorful artwork and traditional decor. With its delicious food and beautiful setting, Lusin is sure to be a memorable dining experience. So why wait? Make a reservation at Lusin today and embark on a culinary journey to Armenia.

name: برج الحمام
description:
Our journey began in 1979, Takhassussi Road in the neighborhood of King Faisal Specialist Hospital and Research Center in Riyadh, where we launched Burj Al Hamam Restaurant to offer the highly demanded traditional Lebanese cuisine.
With the sit-down and take-away concept becoming more popular, we opened an outlet on Orouba Road in the mid 1980’s. Building on its success and growth, an express take-away outlet was launched in the food court of the prestigious Al-Faisaliah shopping mall in 1999.
With its uncompromised quality and exceptional service, Burj Al Hamam’s name became synonymous with the finest Lebanese cuisine and catering, especially among Saudi nationals.

name: مطعم لوسين
description: Lusin Restaurant is a unique dining experience that transports you to the vibrant culture of Armenia. Our menu features a wide range of traditional Armenian dishes, each expertly crafted to showcase the unique flavors and aromas of this rich and vibrant culture. From savory kebabs and stuffed grape leaves, to sweet pastries and aromatic coffee, there is something for everyone at Lusin. As you dine, enjoy the lively Armenian music and take in the cultural atmosphere of the restaurant, which is adorned with colorful artwork and traditional decor. With its delicious food and beautiful setting, Lusin is sure to be a memorable dining experience. So why wait? Make a reservation at Lusin today and embark on a culinary journey to Armenia.

name: انتروكوت كافيه دو باريس
description:
The Original Franchise from Geneva Since 1930
The FIRST Entrecôte Restaurant in Riyadh, Al Faisaliah Tower, where you can enjoy the real Entrecôte steak amazing taste, fabulous atmosphere & great Riyadh view

The sauce “Café de Paris” developed by Mr. Boubier in 1930 to accompany the faux fillet steak (Entrecôte) at his restaurant in Geneva enabled him to launch an astonishing concept offering a single menu formula that gained an immediate worldwide success.

The ingredients of this sauce are still secret till today. Mr. François Voulliamoz, the owner of the original Entrecôte “Café de Paris” restaurant in Geneva, Rue Mont Blanc is the only person in the world who holds the secret of this sauce as it originated in 1930.

Now in VIA Riyadh!
